		{
			"text": "Security update for Linux Kernel Live Patch 4 for SLE 12 SP2",
			"title": "Topic",
			"type": "Summary"
		},
		{
			"text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.4.38-93 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security bugs were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2017-1000364: An issue was discovered in the size of the stack guard page on Linux, specifically a 4k stack guard page is not sufficiently large and can be 'jumped' over (the stack guard page is bypassed) (bsc#1039496).\n",
			"title": "Details",
			"type": "General"
